The Index8 pixel format could, and often does, support colors. As a result, an automatic switch is not possible.

However, this is just the default in-memory representation if it can't be detected. If you know you have only gray images, then you can decode to a gray 8 by intercepting the values:

```csharp
var codec =  SKCodec.Create(data);
var newInfo = new SKImageInfo(codec.Info.Width, codec.Info.Height, SKColorType.Gray8);
var bitmap = SKBitmap.Decode(codec, newInfo);
```
